{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Consensus threshold can be bypassed with duplicated signer entries","locations":["permissions/Consensus.sol:23","permissions/Consensus.sol:26","permissions/Consensus.sol:47"],"claim":"`checkSignatures` only enforces `signatures.length >= threshold` and validates each element independently; it never enforces signer uniqueness. The same authorized signer/signature can be repeated to satisfy threshold.","impact":"Multisig guarantees collapse for all `Consensus`-gated flows. Operations meant to require N distinct signers can be executed with fewer real signers, enabling unauthorized signature-queue deposits/redeems.","paths":["Configure threshold > 1 with at least one valid signer","Submit signatures array containing duplicate entries for that signer","`checkSignatures` returns true and privileged order executes"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Deposit cancellation uses oracle checkpoint value as Fenwick index","locations":["queues/DepositQueue.sol:107","queues/DepositQueue.sol:114"],"claim":"`cancelDepositRequest` reads `(exists, timestamp, index)` from `prices.latestCheckpoint()`, but for `Checkpoints.Trace224` the third return value is the checkpoint value (`priceD18`), not the request-tree index. That value is incorrectly used in `requests.modify(index, -assets)`.","impact":"Cancellations can revert (out-of-bounds Fenwick index) after reports exist, causing effective lockup of pending requests. In other states, subtraction may hit the wrong bucket and corrupt aggregate queue accounting.","paths":["User creates deposit request","Before claimability, user calls `cancelDepositRequest`","Function uses `priceD18` as Fenwick index in `requests.modify`, causing revert or wrong-bucket mutation"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Transfer whitelist check is inverted","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:138","managers/ShareManager.sol:139"],"claim":"With transfer whitelist enabled, `updateChecks` reverts when `from.canTransfer` is true or `to.canTransfer` is false. This inverts sender policy: non-transferable senders can pass if receiver is transferable, while transferable senders are blocked.","impact":"Transfer restriction policy is mis-enforced, allowing unauthorized transfers and blocking authorized ones.","paths":["Enable `hasTransferWhitelist`","Set sender `canTransfer=false` and recipient `canTransfer=true`","Sender transfer passes despite being non-transfer-whitelisted"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Signature queues bypass global queue pause","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:11","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:13","modules/ShareModule.sol:183"],"claim":"Standard deposit/redeem queues check `isPausedQueue(address(this))`, but signature queue entrypoints do not. Pausing a queue in `ShareModule` does not stop `SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` / `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem`.","impact":"Emergency queue pause is ineffective for signature-based flows, allowing continued state-changing operations during incidents.","paths":["Admin pauses queue with `setQueueStatus(queue, true)`","User submits signature-queue order","Order still executes because entrypoint lacks pause check"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Auto-claim on token updates can become gas-prohibitive with many queues/assets","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:234","modules/ShareModule.sol:238","modules/ShareModule.sol:242","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:46","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:49","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:52"],"claim":"`claimShares` iterates all assets and all deposit queues. `TokenizedShareManager._update` calls `claimShares` for both `from` and `to` on every transfer/mint/burn, creating O(assets*queues) overhead per token movement.","impact":"As queue/asset count grows, ordinary share transfers can exceed gas limits and fail, creating liveness failures for tokenized share operations.","paths":["Protocol accumulates many assets/queues","Any transfer triggers `_update` -> `claimShares(from)` and `claimShares(to)`","Nested iteration and external queue calls make transfers revert from gas exhaustion"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Permissionless one-time `setVault` can be initialization-hijacked in non-atomic deployments","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:167","managers/RiskManager.sol:147","oracles/Oracle.sol:90","vaults/VaultConfigurator.sol:70"],"claim":"`setVault` is externally callable and only guarded by one-time initialization (`vault == 0`). If deployment/configuration is not atomic, an external caller can front-run and permanently bind a component to the wrong vault.","impact":"Initialization can be griefed or hijacked, potentially bricking intended deployment flows and forcing redeployments.","paths":["Component proxy is deployed with unset vault","Attacker calls `setVault(attackerVault)` first","Legitimate configurator call reverts with `InvalidInitialization`"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Protocol fee can be minted multiple times per period by reporting non-base assets","locations":["managers/FeeManager.sol:81","managers/FeeManager.sol:83","managers/FeeManager.sol:119","modules/ShareModule.sol:281","modules/ShareModule.sol:285"],"claim":"`calculateFee` applies protocol time-based accrual for every `handleReport` call using `timestamps[vault]`, but `updateState` only advances that timestamp when `asset == baseAsset`. Non-base asset reports therefore repeatedly charge the same elapsed interval before a base-asset report updates the checkpoint.","impact":"Repeated reporting across non-base assets can over-mint fee shares for the same time window, causing material dilution and value extraction to the fee recipient.","paths":["Timestamp checkpoint is stale for a vault","Oracle submits report(s) for non-base asset(s): each `handleReport` mints protocol fee from the same elapsed interval","Only later base-asset report updates timestamp, after over-accrual has already occurred"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Performance fee is charged on price drawdowns instead of gains","locations":["managers/FeeManager.sol:77","managers/FeeManager.sol:78","managers/FeeManager.sol:123","managers/FeeManager.sol:124"],"claim":"`calculateFee` mints performance fee when `priceD18 < minPriceD18`, and `updateState` tracks/updates a running minimum. This charges performance fees on new lows rather than on appreciation.","impact":"Users are diluted during negative performance; repeated lower prices can trigger repeated performance-fee minting, inverting expected fee economics.","paths":["Base-asset min price exists from prior reports","New lower base-asset report arrives and `calculateFee` mints performance fee","`updateState` lowers `minPriceD18`, enabling repeated fee minting on subsequent lower lows"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Disallowing a subvault asset can permanently lock already-held funds","locations":["managers/RiskManager.sol:242","managers/RiskManager.sol:243","modules/VaultModule.sol:147","modules/VaultModule.sol:148"],"claim":"`modifySubvaultBalance` reverts for any asset not in `allowedAssets[subvault]`, regardless of direction. After governance removes an asset via `disallowSubvaultAssets`, later negative balance updates needed for pulls (`_pullAssets`) also revert.","impact":"Assets already held in a subvault can become non-withdrawable after disallowing, creating permanent lockup unless special recovery exists.","paths":["Subvault holds asset X","Governance disallows X for that subvault","Any later pull path calling `modifySubvaultBalance(subvault, X, negative)` reverts with `NotAllowedAsset`"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Redeem hook can be griefed by dusting disallowed subvaults","locations":["hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:19","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:24","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:39","managers/RiskManager.sol:242","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:178","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:194"],"claim":"`BasicRedeemHook` treats raw ERC20 balances in all subvaults as liquid and tries to pull from any subvault with positive balance. If a subvault is not allowed for that asset, `hookPullAssets` reaches `modifySubvaultBalance` and reverts with `NotAllowedAsset`.","impact":"An attacker can dust tokens into a disallowed subvault and cause redemption batch handling to revert, creating permissionless DoS on affected redeem flows using this hook.","paths":["Attacker transfers dust of redeem asset A to subvault S that disallows A","Hook counts S balance as liquid and attempts pull during redeem processing","RiskManager rejects pull for disallowed asset, reverting batch handling"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Deposit accounting assumes exact ERC20 transfers and breaks on fee-on-transfer tokens","locations":["libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:46","queues/DepositQueue.sol:77","queues/DepositQueue.sol:91","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:14","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:18"],"claim":"ERC20 receive paths trust requested amount and do not check actual token delta after transfer. For taxed/deflationary tokens, internal accounting and minted shares are based on nominal amount while actual received amount is lower.","impact":"If such assets are supported, the protocol can mint excess shares versus real assets received, causing dilution and potential insolvency/failed redemptions.","paths":["User deposits fee-on-transfer token","Queue records/mints against full requested amount","Vault receives less than accounted, creating an accounting deficit"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Signature redeem can burn shares from arbitrary recipients without recipient-bound authorization","locations":["queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:22","queues/SignatureQueue.sol:98"],"claim":"`validateOrder` only binds `order.caller` to `msg.sender` and nonce/signatures, while `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem` burns `order.recipient` shares. There is no on-chain requirement that the burned account authorized this redemption (e.g., recipient signature or `recipient == caller`).","impact":"If signer policy/process is compromised or misconfigured, third-party accounts can be forcibly redeemed at signer-approved terms, causing involuntary exits and economic harm.","paths":["Submit a consensus-signed redeem order with `caller=executor` and `recipient=victim`","Validation passes because caller/nonce/signatures are valid","Queue burns victim shares and transfers redemption assets to victim, forcing an unwanted unwind"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-014","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Removing an oracle-supported asset can brick queue/risk flows and lock funds","locations":["oracles/Oracle.sol:64","oracles/Oracle.sol:153","managers/RiskManager.sol:108","queues/DepositQueue.sol:113","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:195","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:20"],"claim":"`removeSupportedAssets` deletes support/report state without checking for active queues, pending requests, or existing balances. `RiskManager.convertToShares` hard-reverts via `oracle.getReport(asset)` for unsupported assets, and several core queue settlement/cancellation paths depend on it.","impact":"After removal, affected operations can revert (pending deposit cancellation, redeem batch handling, vault balance updates), creating stuck accounting and realistic fund lockup for that asset.","paths":["Privileged actor removes an asset still used by queues/positions","Subsequent flows call `RiskManager.convertToShares(asset, ...)`","`oracle.getReport(asset)` reverts `UnsupportedAsset`, bricking settlement/cancelation paths"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Permissionless claiming allows third parties to impose targeted-lockup timing on victims","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:234","queues/DepositQueue.sol:120","managers/ShareManager.sol:180","managers/ShareManager.sol:229"],"claim":"`ShareModule.claimShares(account)` and `DepositQueue.claim(account)` are callable by anyone for arbitrary users. When claim mints shares, `ShareManager.mint` sets `accounts[account].lockedUntil = block.timestamp + targetedLockup`, letting third parties choose when that lock window starts.","impact":"If `targetedLockup` is enabled, attackers can front-run user actions and force lock activation at adverse times, temporarily blocking victim transfers/burns (including previously-held active shares) and causing targeted denial-of-use.","paths":["Victim has claimable deposit shares and `targetedLockup` is non-zero","Attacker calls `claimShares(victim)` or `DepositQueue.claim(victim)` before victim’s planned transfer/redeem","Claim mints and refreshes `lockedUntil`, making victim’s next transfer/burn revert until expiry"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Signature queues bypass configured deposit/redeem fee hooks","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:21","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:22","queues/DepositQueue.sol:167","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:100"],"claim":"Standard queues apply fee logic via `FeeManager.calculateDepositFee` / `calculateRedeemFee` during report handling or redeem request processing, but signature queues mint/burn directly from order fields and never invoke those fee calculations.","impact":"Signature-routed order flow can execute at economics inconsistent with configured queue fee policy, reducing expected fee capture and creating different effective pricing versus regular queue users.","paths":["Execute a signed order through `SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` with `order.requested` set to full quoted shares and no fee deduction path.","Execute a signed order through `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem` with `order.ordered` burned and no `calculateRedeemFee` mint-to-recipient path."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"CUSTOM_VERIFIER payload parsing expects a different wire format than documented packed encoding","locations":["permissions/Verifier.sol:115","permissions/Verifier.sol:117","permissions/Verifier.sol:119"],"claim":"CUSTOM_VERIFIER execution reads the verifier address using a full 32-byte `calldataload` at `verificationData.offset` and forwards `verificationData[0x20:]` as verifier-specific payload. This matches a 32-byte padded address prefix, not a packed `address || data` format.","impact":"If operators build Merkle leaves and calldata using the documented packed layout, custom-verifier calls can fail verification at runtime and block authorized `CallModule.call` operations until payload generation is changed.","paths":["Build `verificationData` as packed `address + verifierData` for a CUSTOM_VERIFIER leaf.","Submit call with valid proof for that payload.","Verifier decodes an incorrect verifier/payload slice and delegated verification fails, reverting the call."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-018","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Vault-subvault accounting assumes exact ERC20 transfer amounts","locations":["modules/VaultModule.sol:147","modules/VaultModule.sol:153","modules/SubvaultModule.sol:33","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:31"],"claim":"`_pushAssets` and `_pullAssets` update risk accounting using the requested `value` and then perform token transfers without measuring actual received deltas. Fee-on-transfer/deflationary behavior can move less than `value` while accounting assumes full movement.","impact":"Subvault exposure and available-liquidity accounting can drift from real balances, causing limit checks to rely on inflated values and creating later pull/redeem failures or effective shortfalls.","paths":["Push a taxed token from vault to subvault via `_pushAssets`; risk state increases by full `value` while subvault receives less.","Subsequent pulls/redeems rely on overstated accounting and fail when trying to source missing tokens."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-019","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Payable ERC20 queue entrypoints can permanently trap accidental ETH","locations":["queues/DepositQueue.sol:59","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:11","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:13","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:40"],"claim":"For non-ETH assets, `receiveAssets` does not enforce `msg.value == 0`. Multiple queue entrypoints are `payable`, so extra ETH is accepted while logic continues with ERC20 accounting only.","impact":"Users/integrators can accidentally send ETH alongside ERC20 queue calls and have it stranded in queue contracts with no recovery path.","paths":["Call an ERC20 queue function with nonzero `msg.value`.","ERC20 transfer path executes successfully and the ETH remains stuck in the queue contract."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-020","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Anyone can steal pending deposit allocations via unrestricted `mintAllocatedShares`","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:212","managers/ShareManager.sol:214","managers/ShareManager.sol:219"],"claim":"`mintAllocatedShares(address,uint256)` is externally callable with no `onlyQueue`/`onlyVault`/role restriction. Any account can consume the global `allocatedShares` pool and mint it to an arbitrary recipient.","impact":"Attackers can front-run legitimate claims and drain shares reserved for depositors, causing direct value theft and making later claims revert with `InsufficientAllocatedShares`.","paths":["Queue report processing calls `allocateShares`, increasing global `allocatedShares`","Attacker calls `mintAllocatedShares(attacker, allocatedShares())`","Legitimate depositor claims later fail or receive reduced value because allocation was already consumed"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-021","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Redeem batches can be marked handled without verifying actual assets received by queue","locations":["queues/RedeemQueue.sol:193","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:198","modules/ShareModule.sol:265","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:31"],"claim":"`handleBatches` assumes `vault.callHook(demand)` followed by vault->queue transfer delivers exactly `demand` assets, then advances `batchIterator` and decreases pending totals. No post-transfer balance delta check exists.","impact":"With non-exact transfer behavior (e.g., fee-on-transfer/deflationary tokens), batches may become claimable while queue is underfunded, leading to claim reverts and practical redemption lock/DoS for affected batches.","paths":["Redeem demand is computed for claimable batches","`callHook(demand)` triggers `TransferLibrary.sendAssets(asset, queue, demand)` but queue receives less than `demand`","`handleBatches` still advances iterator and marks those batches handled","User claims later attempt to transfer unavailable assets and revert"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-101","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Removing a deposit queue can permanently lock already-processed but unclaimed shares","locations":["queues/DepositQueue.sol:44","modules/ShareModule.sol:215","modules/ShareModule.sol:234","queues/DepositQueue.sol:136","managers/ShareManager.sol:223"],"claim":"`DepositQueue.canBeRemoved()` only checks processing progress (`handledIndices == timestamps.length()`), not whether users have actually claimed. After `removeQueue`, claim execution reaches `ShareManager.mint` through `mintAllocatedShares`, but `mint` enforces `onlyVaultOrQueue` and the removed queue no longer satisfies `hasQueue`, so claims from that queue revert.","impact":"A privileged queue-removal action can strand claimable deposits in an unclaimable state, causing practical permanent lockup of user entitlements from that queue.","paths":["Deposits are handled and shares are allocated, but some users have not yet called claim","Authorized actor removes the deposit queue once `canBeRemoved()` returns true","User later calls `DepositQueue.claim(account)`","`mintAllocatedShares` invokes `mint`, `onlyVaultOrQueue` fails because the queue was removed, and claim reverts"],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-102","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Native-ETH sentinel asset configuration can DoS redeem liquidity checks","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:150","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:11","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:35","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:178","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:18","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:20"],"claim":"The system supports a native-ETH sentinel asset in `TransferLibrary`, but redeem liquidity paths call `IERC20(asset).balanceOf(...)` (`ShareModule.getLiquidAssets` when no hook, and `BasicRedeemHook.getLiquidAssets/callHook`). For the ETH sentinel this is not a valid ERC20 target and can revert during ABI decode/call.","impact":"If a queue is configured with the ETH sentinel asset, redeem handling and signature-redeem prechecks can become uncallable, causing withdrawal denial and potential lockup for affected users.","paths":["Configure/create redeem flow for `TransferLibrary.ETH` asset","Call `RedeemQueue.handleBatches` or `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem`","Flow calls `vault.getLiquidAssets()` and executes ERC20 `balanceOf` against ETH sentinel","Call reverts and redeem processing cannot proceed"],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-103","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Role fallback in `onlyQueueOrRole` is broken for non-queue callers","locations":["managers/RiskManager.sol:49","modules/ShareModule.sol:56","modules/ShareModule.sol:57","managers/RiskManager.sol:206","managers/RiskManager.sol:224"],"claim":"`onlyQueueOrRole` first evaluates `IShareModule(vault).hasQueue(caller)`. `hasQueue` calls `IQueue(caller).asset()` unconditionally, which can revert for EOAs/multisigs/non-queue contracts before the role check runs. As a result, role-authorized operators cannot reliably call queue-or-role guarded functions unless they are queue contracts.","impact":"Intended emergency/reconciliation operations (`modifyPendingAssets`, `modifyVaultBalance`) may be inaccessible to governance/ops role holders during incidents, prolonging accounting drift and operational disruption.","paths":["Grant `MODIFY_PENDING_ASSETS_ROLE` or `MODIFY_VAULT_BALANCE_ROLE` to an operator account that is not a queue contract","Operator calls `modifyPendingAssets` or `modifyVaultBalance`","`hasQueue(caller)` reverts while trying `IQueue(caller).asset()`","Execution reverts before role fallback is evaluated"],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-201","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Tokenized lockup is bypassable via auto-claim ordering in `_update`","locations":["managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:47","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:49","managers/ShareManager.sol:229","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:98"],"claim":"`TokenizedShareManager._update` performs `updateChecks(from,to)` before `claimShares(from)`. If `claimShares` mints pending deposit shares, `mint` sets a fresh `lockedUntil` only after checks, and the same update still completes transfer/burn.","impact":"Users can move or redeem newly claimed shares immediately in the same transaction, bypassing targeted lockup/cooldown enforcement.","paths":["User has claimable deposit shares and `targetedLockup > 0`.","User calls redeem/transfer that triggers `_update(from, ..., value)`.","`updateChecks` passes using pre-claim lock state, then `claimShares(from)` mints and sets new lock.","Operation still burns/transfers those freshly claimed shares in the same call."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-202","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Signature deposits bypass depositor whitelist checks on the caller","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:12","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:21","queues/DepositQueue.sol:69"],"claim":"`SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` never verifies `isDepositorWhitelisted(order.caller, ...)`; it validates signatures and then mints to `order.recipient`. The whitelist gate in `ShareManager.updateChecks` applies to the recipient on mint, not the caller providing funds.","impact":"If operators rely on depositor-side whitelist restrictions, non-whitelisted callers can still route deposits through signature flow by directing shares to an allowed recipient, weakening access-control/compliance assumptions.","paths":["A non-whitelisted caller obtains valid consensus signatures for an order with a whitelisted recipient.","Caller submits `SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` and transfers assets.","Mint succeeds for recipient without any caller-whitelist verification path."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-203","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Blacklist is not enforced for transfer recipients","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:131","managers/ShareManager.sol:134"],"claim":"In transfer flow (`from != 0 && to != 0`), `updateChecks` verifies blacklist status for `from` but does not check whether `to` is blacklisted.","impact":"Blacklisted accounts can still receive shares, violating send/receive blacklist expectations and enabling policy bypass.","paths":["A non-blacklisted holder transfers shares to a blacklisted address.","Transfer passes because only sender blacklist status is checked."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-204","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"First report for a newly supported asset is always marked suspicious","locations":["oracles/Oracle.sol:199","oracles/Oracle.sol:116","oracles/Oracle.sol:124"],"claim":"When an asset has no prior report (`prevPriceD18 == 0`), `_validatePrice` always returns `(true, true)`. As a result, `submitReports` records the report as suspicious and skips `vault.handleReport`; progressing that asset requires a separate `acceptReport` call.","impact":"Newly added assets have a hard operational dependency on `ACCEPT_REPORT_ROLE`; if that path is unavailable, queue/risk processing for the asset can remain stuck.","paths":["Governance adds a new supported asset with empty report history.","Reporter submits the first price via `submitReports`; it is flagged suspicious and not forwarded to vault handling.","Without a successful `acceptReport`, asset-specific processing does not advance."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"BasicRedeemHook.getLiquidAssets uses msg.sender instead of address(this)","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"In protocol flow `getLiquidAssets` is called by `ShareModule`, so `msg.sender` is intentionally the vault context. Using `address(this)` there would point to the hook contract and return incorrect balances."}]}
